quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  2,113,"Nevertheless, the Jews said, “Christians have no ground whatsoever to stand on,” while the Christians said, “Jews have no ground whatsoever to stand on.” Yet they read the Scripture. Similarly, the ones who do not know said the like of their saying. Thus Allah judges between them on the Day of Resurrection regarding whatever they differed over."
  2,114,"And who is more unjust than one who prevented<i class=""s"">(praying in) </i>the mosques of Allah so that His Name be not mentioned in them, and pursued their ruin? Those—never was it for them to enter them except in fear. For them is disgrace in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>, and for them in the Hereafter is a great punishment."
  2,115,"And to Allah belong the East and the West, so wherever you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>turn, then that is where Allah’s Countenance is. Indeed, Allah is All-Embracing, All-Knowing."
  2,116,"<span class="h">And they{1}</span><span class=""h"">said</span>, “Allah has taken<i class=""s"">(for Himself) </i>offspring.” Highly Exalted is He. Rather, to Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth; all are devout towards Him—",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “They said,”</span>
  2,117,"the Innovator of the heavens and the earth, and whenever He decrees a matter, He only says to it, <span class="h">“Be,” and so it is{1}</span>.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “He only says to it, ‘Be,’ so it is.”</span>
  2,118,"And those who do not know said, “If only Allah would speak to us, or a sign would come to us.” Thus said those who were before them—just what they said. Their hearts are alike. We have certainly made the signs evident for people who are certain."
  2,119,"We have indeed sent you with the truth as a herald of glad tidings and as a warner, <span class="h">for you will not be asked{1}</span>about the fellows of purgatory.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’ and Ya’qub read it as: “…as a warner, so do not ask about the fellows of purgatory.”</span>
